description.plain:
Dinah Jane Milika Ilaisaane Hansen Amasio was born in Santa Ana, California on June 22, 1997 to parents Gordon and Milika Fot'aika. She and her six younger siblings are of Polynesian, Tongan, and Danish descent.

She released her first single, “Dancing Like A White Girl,” on iTunes and Spotify in 2011 before auditioning for The X Factor in 2012, singing “If I Were a Boy” by Beyoncé and was complimented by judge L.A. Reid stating she “took the song to places that even Beyoncé didn’t.”

Through X Factor, she became part of the multi-platinum girl group Fifth Harmony, producing hits like “Worth It,” “Work From Home,” along with her fellow bandmates, Lauren Jauregui, Ally Brooke, Normani Kordei, and Camila Cabello.

Her solo projects from the group started with a feature on RedOne’s “Boom Boom” alongside Daddy Yankee and French Montana, released on the 27th of October in 2017.

description.plain:
“Bottled Up” is the debut solo single from Dinah Jane. It’s her first song as a lead artist and the first song she’s released since Fifth Harmony went on a hiatus. It’s about someone who turns to smoking and drinking in order to get their “bottled up” feelings out.

Dinah sees it as a “transition single” from her 5H times to her solo endeavors:

I feel like ‘Bottled Up’ was something I just wanted to get off my chest — the transition from Fifth Harmony to Dinah and I just didn’t want to lose my fans so I kind of kept some familiar sounds in there and now I’m honing into more of what I will be releasing

The song features Marc E. Bassy and Ty Dolla $ign, making it the second time Dinah and Ty have collaborated on a song–the first time being Fifth Harmony’s hit single “Work From Home”.

This song has been teased a couple of times before its release–the first time being back in November, 2017. Later in August 2018, a video of her on the set of the music video with Ty and Marc was released–which was later released as the song’s official lyric video.

description.plain:
“Retrograde” was the second song released by singer-songwriter Dinah Jane, released as a promotional single on Youtube.  She first performed this song live on Jingle Bash on December 3, 2018. A music video for the track was officially released on March 26, 2019, and the song was made available in all streaming platforms on May, 8.

Most fans were surprised with the release as Dinah had been radio silent on social media a few weeks prior. In an interview to Music Choice, DJ confessed that it was fan pressure that eventually convinced her to release the song.

She left the following message to her fans on her social media accounts:

A lil pick me up since mercury is in RETROGRADE! As you know, I’ve been hard at work in the studio, and I promise you, new music is coming SOON! I appreciate you all for being so patient with me and for always lifting me up. I wanted to say thank you and to share something with you NOW, to hold you over until the new tracks drop… I heard YOU and saw all of your amazing feedback and comments when I performed “Retrograde” at iHeart. So here it is!

description.plain:
“Fix It” is about Dinah’s relationship with her family. She’s the eldest of seven children and, up until the The X Factor US and joining Fifth Harmony, lived with about 20 people of her family in only one house. However close she was to her family, there have been some issues regarding her career and performances in 5H. Eventually, her family’s lack of support became toxic:

They were afraid of me failing, of me being an embarrassment. So me performing in certain things, or saying certain things in certain records — they kind of looked away from it, because they were like, ‘what are you doing?’

As the song is about a delicate subject, Dinah didn’t want to release it, but was convinced otherwise by her label’s CEO, L.A. Reid:

L.A. [Reid] told me, ‘This is the most personal song I’ve ever heard in my life. I think you should release it. And I thought, ‘You know what? It’s time I let people know what’s going on and what my truth is.

When Dinah showed “Fix It” to her family, their reaction was to apologize for the situation. Dinah even claims that “Fix It” saved her relationship with her family:

They caved in and they were like… we can never fight or never make you become something you’re not, so you just be you. This song was something that saved us, in a way, from being even more toxic… It’s the most personal I’ve ever gotten in the studio with a producer and writer.

songs.title: Missed a Spot

description.plain:
“Missed A Spot” is a song by American singer, Dinah Jane. The song is the third record that Dinah has released in under a month along with “1501” and “Lottery.

The song was first teased in an Instagram Story on Dinah’s Instagram and then later teased again in an acoustic performance on Instagram Live.

In a interview with MTV News, Dinah talked about the idea of the song’s music video by saying:

I started seeing the whole music video. The reason we added those elements into the record is because of what I was seeing in my vision, And being that I have my Polynesian background, I wanted it to be tropical, I wanted you to feel like you were somewhere else. You weren’t home. You were on vacation. That was the whole setting that I saw. And you’re surrounded by Polynesian women performing for you."

Due to the ongoing 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic, the filming for the music video has been on hold.

description.plain: “Ya Ya” is Dinah Jane’s comeback to music after more than 3 years of absence. Speaking to People Magazine, Dinah shared that she had actually quit music during this period, recalling that “there was that inner voice of, ‘Who are you? Who do you want to be? […] All these questions started kicking me down at the time, and I was like, 'I honestly quit.’ I told my family, ‘I don’t want this no more. I don’t care for music.’”. She also mentioned her then-upcoming participation in a writing camp in celebration of Asian American & Pacific Islanders Heritage Month, where the song was ultimately created with previous Fifth Harmony collaborator, Chris ‘Flict’ Aparri.

description.plain:
Dinah Jane peformed a cover of Beyoncé’s “If I Were a Boy” on her audition for The X Factor USA 2012. She made it to the next stage of the competition and was eventually put in a girl group named Fifth Harmony.

The feedback was very positive. LA Reid praised her performance, saying that Dinah took that song “places even Beyoncé couldn’t take”. Britney said that Dinah “made her day” with her singing. Demi claimed to have had the “chills” while Dinah was singing and told her she would go very far. Simon ended the feedback session by telling Dinah that her family was going to be proud of her.

In an interview to TERRELL, Dinah revealed that “If I Were a Boy” wasn’t her first song choice for her audition:

The first song I sang was “I’d Rather Go Blind”, by Etta James. Simon Cowell stopped towards the end when I was about to hit this really good note and he said: ‘Do you have another song?’. I kept listing all other songs that I had – Jessie J’s “Big White Room”, “Listen”, from Beyoncé, a Mariah Carey one. And then the last one was “If I Were a Boy”, but I had never rehearsed it.
